# Environment Variables - Supabase Configuration
# Copy this file to frontend/.env.local and update with your actual values

# ===========================
# Supabase Configuration
# ===========================

# Get these from your Supabase project dashboard: Settings > API
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# ===========================
# Deployment
# ===========================

# Frontend: Vercel
# - Set VITE_SUPABASE_URL and VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY in Vercel dashboard
# - Project Settings > Environment Variables

# Backend: Supabase (managed)
# - Database, Auth, and Storage are handled by Supabase
# - Configure RLS policies in Supabase SQL Editor

# ===========================
# Notes
# ===========================

# 1. Never commit .env.local to version control
# 2. The anon key is safe to expose in frontend code (RLS protects data)
# 3. Never expose the service_role key in frontend code
